@NODE Alco
@{b}@{u}AlcoRhythm@{ub}@{uu}

Alco "Rhythm" Lammers is the sampler and module composer.
He's 18 years old and studies at the MTS in D'chem.
He is a Hellraiser/Jurassic Park fanatic... (strange combination huh?)
Most of all (and we always forgot to put it in the Doc) he is a fan
of Stephen King. Yes, the king of horror!

@{b}Quote...@{ub}
"I think that the one thing that keeps me going, are the reactions (mainly
positive) to our mods. Together with Solution I spent a lot of time,
creating what I think, is good music (using a good computer! Thnx C=!!!).
Before that, I spent even more time on my keyboard (all by my self, in the
dark, I hate light) trying to find the right tune for the next mod.
If it wasn't for your reactions, I would have given up making mods a long
time ago.
It's really frustrating to realise how boring my life seems from the
outside. But if you where me, I am sure you wouldn't want it any different.
There is only one thing I am scared of: What if something happens to me, so
I can't make music anymore. What if my hearing wears off. I can't live
without (my) music. And right now, I notice that I forgot to turn on the
radio (I'm dying!)..."

					Signed AlcoRhythm...
@ENDNODE



@NODE Thijs
@{b}@{u}Solution@{ub}@{uu}

Thijs "Solution" Stalenhoef is a sampler and does some module work.
He's also responsible for distributing the stuff.
He is 1 of the sample sources of @{b}The Problem@{ub}!
Besides that he's Moderator of NLA_CHAT & NLA_AUDIO. 
He's 17 and studies at the CCS VWO in Aalten.
Together with his partner Monique Meekes he has won lots of prizes in
dance-contests...

@{b}Quote...@{ub}
"Music and dancing means LIFE to me...If I didn't have my module work
together with Alcorhythm I wouldn't be as much a human being as now!
When I get back from school I NEED some Techno/Breakbeat/Dance music.
It powers me up you see...Dancing too! People who see me dancing usually
think I'm nutz or drunk or both! They are simply too narrowminded to see
this is LIFE!!! Therefore I'd like to thank my partner in DANCE:
@{b}Monique@{ub} for her support in keeping my life going. All you people 
out there that have down'd our mods, keep up the good work and thnx 4 your 
support! Trance is also important, but in western society it is seen 
as something bad/weird/demonic. On the floor you go with the flow and 
your brain expands to cosmic proportions. 
Something else: When you buy records: LISTEN to them...do not only think
"Well...They're famous" or "Well...It has a nice bassline/beat". NO! Listen
to what the music has to offer. Listen to the whole concept and see the
record as a whole! House is a FEELING!!! (And that is something some
babyboomers/house-haters simply do not WANT to understand!!!)
House music as a whole is going through bad times! 
Organizing a party is getting tougher everyday! So if we
stick together and form ONE front we can DO something about it!
The 'drug problem' is probably the biggest argument against! But there is
no drug problem! I have NEVER seen a fight during a good party! (Either
completely Underground or out in the open, but then with support from the
city-counsel!) But in discos there are nothing BUT fights! During one party
I stepped on the toes of some person I wouldn't want to meet at night in a
small alley, but HE embraced me (yes he did) and said "Sorry Gabber, won't
happen again...". You try and give a similar example for a night in a
disco! So...Legalize (soft-) drugs like hashies and XTC, this will also
prevent trash-xtc to enter the market.
For now: Let us go back to 1988, The SUMMER OF LOVE! 
Peace, Love, Unity and RAVE!!!
Stay tuned for more stuff from me, Alco and the rest..."

				       __	Signed:
			              (          
				       \ OLUTION
        		             ___) 				      

@ENDNODE




@NODE William
@{b}@{u}DJ Infinity@{ub}@{uu}

William "Infinity" Westrum is a sample source for @{b}The Problem@{ub} 
And when I say sample source, I mean SAMPLE source (He's got 100s of CDs!!!)
He's 18 years old. He studies at the CCS HAVO, Aalten.
When @{b}The Problem@{ub} needs to record their work on tape, The DJ
supplies the audiomixing equipment.
He's got a girlfriend......

@{b}Quote...@{ub}

@ENDNODE



@NODE Wanda
@{b}@{u}Wanda@{uu}

Wanda@{ub} is the first woman that joined @{b}The Problem@{ub}. 
She is 19 and has long blond hair. 
She's a singer (listen to Wanda,Wanda2,Enraptor) and she sometimes helps
with the module work of the rest of @{b}The Problem@{ub} dries up.
She's about 1.76m and she studies at a MEAO in a town not far from the HQ!
In her spare time she used to be a maid...
(Read Wanda&CSilla) 

@{b}Quote...@{ub}
"Oh, I'm so happy these days! My work with @{b}The Problem@{ub} is truly
fantastic. It helped a great deal in rebuilding my life after I had some
really hard times. Thnx Solution, CSilla, William and Alcorhythm too! 
Your music has made my life worthwhile again.
Let everybody be them selfs and stop wearing masks! House is here, and it
is here to stay!!! To all you political persons out there: Damn You!!!
Everyone must be free to choose the form of music they like, and mine (and
@{b}The Problem@{ub}s) just happens to be house, SO WHAT!?
Luv to ALL who supported us (Also Alcos mother for suppling Bugles all the
time!) in one way or another!
I send you my love..."                                   
                                                          (\/)
                                        Signed:            \/
                                 (\/)
                                  \/      \/\/anda....

                                                (\/)
                                                 \/

@ENDNODE


@NODE CSilla
@{b}@{u}CSilla@{ub}@{uu}

She joined @{b}The Problem@{ub}, but she hasn't done much yet, besides
giving Solution and Alcorhythm (and Wanda too to some extent) a LOT of
inspiration... (She is being pushed to start singing too, her voice is
great! => Bjork?)
She's 18 and is the sun in the place! Always happy and cheerful!
Well...She just did her exams at CCS (VWO!) and is probably going to pass
them aswell!!! Almost certainly Enschede University is going to be her
place for the years to come...(The rest will miss her. She'll only be
around weekends!). And then her hair....Solution likes to play with it!
It is long, black and curly...

@{b}Quote...@{ub}
"I have to write this, they said. Because everybody did it! Personally I
don't think it is of no use to tell you who I am. You out there probably
read this because it came with the module. You got that because you want to
hear music, no matter who made it! But allright, I will tell you
something...
First of all: Just LOOK at the world around you! The world you and I have
to live in is not all as bad as it seems! Look at the birds, and smell the
flowers! Life is GREAT! Make wonderful friends (I know I have...) and live
life the best possible way! But...take care for the environment!
@{b}The Problem@{ub} are great guys, although Infinity should stop showing
up late and Alcorhythm should learn to control his tempre. Solution should
stop pushing me to sing for them! I'll sing when I'm ready! (Not now that
is!). Wanda is great too. But she should eat less Bugles...
With kind regards....
		
						Signed:

					          CSilla

@ENDNODE


@NODE Equipment "The Equipment"
@{b}@{u}The Equipment of The Problem@{ub}@{uu}

How do they do it? Here is your answer! A list of all the equipment used by
@{b}The Problem@{ub} :

1. A1200 with 2mb chipmem and 65mb HD.   (storage and tracking use)
2. A1200 with 2mb chipmem and 130mb HD.  (sampling and tracking use)
3. 1 Digimaster Sampler.                 (obvious use)
4. 1 Samsung Midi-Set.                   (CD/12" sampling)
5. 1 Philips Portable Sound thingy.      (cassette sampling)
6. 351+ CDs.				 (they eat CDs!)
7. 1 Stereo Sound Mixer (Alecto Pro 33). (recordings on tape)
8. 'MIDI Master' MIDI Interface.         (composing stuff)
9. 1 @{"GEM WS 2 Keyboard/Workstation." LINK WS2}
@ENDNODE



@NODE WS2 "Keyboard Workstation"
@{b}@{u}The GEM WS2 - Keyboard/Workstation@{ub}@{uu}

This one was so expensive that we'll tell you a little more about it.

@{b}The Problem@{ub} uses this device to compose their melodylines.
They also use it to find out what chords the victims in case of a
replication use. The sounds of the keyboard is often sampled if samples
couldn'd be sampled from the original source. Thanks to GEM!

The @{u}GEM WS 2 Keyboard/Workstation@{uu} is a now somewhat aged Keyboard
with some intelligent stuff in it to make it Workstation.
It has 61 lightweight fullsize keys. There are 128 sounds in it (to wich
you can add another 128). It knows 61 drumsounds, 96 global settings, 32
built in drum patterns and 32 realtime effects.
There is a pitchball, a soundmixing system, MIDI support, a Disk Drive
Option, a (5 way) split function, a 16 note polyphone, a sequencer (with
chain composer), an alpha dial, an audio in/out connection, a 2*20 Watt
built in speaker set and a lot more.

This was probably very boring, but we had to put it in, sorry!
@ENDNODE



