@NODE Mellow "Y(M)ellow Pages..."
@{b}@{u}Mellow@{ub}@{uu}

What the Hell is that???

First off: Mellow is NOT (only) Robin S. (so...C00L it D.S.!)
	   Also, Mellow is NOT 2 Unlimited (god no!)

Mellow is a collection of all types of music (most of them haven't got a
name), that are not @{"Hardcore" LINK Hardcore} or @{"Techno" LINK Techno}! 
It is what you hear when you listen to @{"The PartyNight" LINK 538}.
@{b}
Best examples (10-06-'94) are:

	Country&Western   -   ReIncarnation
	XPress2		  -   Say What!
	2 Phases	  -   Quest 4 Trance
	Slo Moshun        -   @{"Bells of New York" LINK BellsOfNY}
	LuvSpunge	  -   Do You Feel What I'm Feeling?
@{u}
	Joe T. Vanelli feat. @{"CSilla" LINK CSilla}  -  Play With The Voice
@{uu}

Record Labels:

	Junior Boys Own (XPress2)
	Outland         (LuvSpunge)
	Wonka		(DJ Creator)
	Work		(Sil)
@ENDNODE



@NODE Hardcore "BreakBeats / Hardcore"
@{b}@{u}BreakBeat@{uu}

BreakBeat@{ub} is a form of music that originates from the U.K. (To the
West of Neverland, and dicovered by Columbus(? - Ed.) )
It uses a strange pattern in the Drumsection, is very catchy, and
frequently used by @{b}The Problem!
Breakbeats@{ub} are often used together with other music, creating stuff
like Ragga-BreakBeat or Jungle-BreakBeat...
@{b}
There are LOTS of GREAT BreakBeat-Tracks around: 

	The Prodigy     -   All
	Altern8		-   All (@{"Armageddon" LINK Armageddon})
	DJ Hype		-   All
	Acen		-   Close Your Eyes
			-   Trip 2 The Moon
			-   Kaleidascopiclimax
			-   Window In The Sky 
	The Problem	-   @{"Talk" LINK Talk}
			-   @{"The Twilight Zone" LINK Twilight}
			-   @{"Long Term" LINK Delusive}
			

@{u}Buy some TODAY!!!




Hardcore@{uu}

Hardcore@{ub} is music that is mainly fast. Actually, its ONLY fast...
It is even debatable if it IS music...
You can recognize a Hardcore lover by the total absence of any hair.
@{b}
There are SOME good Hardcore tracks:

	Jones & Stephenson   -   The First/Second Rebirth
	DJ Hooligan	     -   All
	And that's it...

Record Labels :
	Bonzai 		(Jones & Stephenson)
@{ub}

The remarks made above, are strictly meant to indicate what @{b}The Problem@{ub}
thinks. They souldn't be interpretated as insults (or something...)
@ENDNODE 

@NODE TECHNO "Techno/Ambient"
@{b}@{u}Techno/Ambient@{ub}@{uu}

This is no place for 2Unlimited!!! (Rule: When there's a video with people
in it shouting "Techno,Techno,Techno" that means it is NOT! - Ed.)
Techno is also a name for a board scope of music types.
There's Intelligent Techno (Under this we also put Ambient) with guys like
Richard D. James (Known as 'Aphex Twin' or 'Polygon Window') and there is
stuff like Hardtrance (So Sven Vaeth and Spicelab) and Acid.(Acid Junkies)
They both aren't mellow or hardcore or breakbeat or 2Unlimited or what
ever. THIS IS A CLASS APART!!!
The music is mostly more abstract (or something)...

@{b}Good Tracks:

			Aphex Twin	- 	On
			Polygon Window	-	Surfing on Sinewaves
			Sven Vaeth	-	An Accident in Paradise
			Spicelab	-	Lost in Spice
			Acid Junkies	-	Paranoid Experience
			Mike Dearborn	-	Chaotic State

Best labels:
				
			Warp (Aphex Twin)
			DJAX-UP (Acid Junkies/Mike Dearborn)
			Harthouse (Spicelab/Sven Vaeth)

@ENDNODE


			
@NODE 538 "Radio 538"
@{b}@{u}The Radio 538 (Now Dance) Partynight@{uu}

The Partynight@{ub} is a great source of inspiration to @{b}The Problem@{ub}
In this night, Radio 538 will play a constant stream of Mellow!
Some of the best DJs around will play their stuff here:
@{b}
			100% Isis
			DJ Marcello
			DJ Jean
		      >	Lucien Foorth <
			Maurits Paardekooper			
			and more...
@{ub}
Although the major event always takes place on Saturday Nights (once in
about 4 weeks), there is ABSOLUTELY no reason why you should not listen!!!
The only valid one, is the one where you just picked up your girl! (Then
listen together!!! - Ed.)
@{b}
Don't miss the next one, just don't!!!@{ub} (tape it...)
@ENDNODE






