@NODE Invention "Mod.Invention"
Replication of a CD Track.
Created after hearing the track on a CD called "Move The House 8".
Try this on 4 size...it's GOOD!
@{b}
Original Title : I Can't Take This
Original Artist: Rhythm Invention@{ub}
@ENDNODE
             
@NODE HellsParty "Mod.Hells_Party" 
Replication of a CD Track.
Created after hearing the track on a CD called "Move The House 8".
At first the samples were taken from a tape, wich made this module somwhat
low quality. This has been corrected, and the final version is incredible!
Very good!
@{b}
Original Title : Hell's Party
Original Artist: GLAM@{ub}
@ENDNODE
         
@NODE Wanda1 "Mod.Wanda"
Cowabunga! Heeere iiis Wandaaa!
First module completely composed by @{b}The Problem@{ub} it self!
Created after hearing a radio commercial for a 'sex o phone'. The Voice
said her name (@{"Wanda" LINK Wanda}) and it was sampled. The beginning of a complete
adventure!
It's great. If u are a House Freak then get a load of this!
@ENDNODE
                  
@NODE LoveParty "Mod.LoveParty"
And now something completely, completely different :-) An ambient xperiment!
Very strange. The only reason this module was released was that it had to
be proved that @{b}The Problem@{ub} could do these SLOW mods to.
However, to keep up the reputation in the House scene, they managed to only
use sounds, sampled from house CDs...
@ENDNODE
         
@NODE GfxAttack "Mod.Grafix-Attack"
Well, this speaks 4 it self.
Created to onor the great @{b}Grafix Attack BBS@{ub}. We were asked to make
a theme, and we did it.
Grafix Attack (BBS) Theme, very nice!!!
@ENDNODE
    
@NODE Armageddon "Mod.Armageddon"
Finally some English Hardcore!!!
@{b}The Problem@{ub} took the challenge and made an 'Altern 8' module.
And it worked out just fine! The resemblence is almost perfect.
Created after hearing the track on the Altern8 Album. Not all samples used
came from this album though (find out wich one!).
@{b}
Original Title : Armageddon
Original Artist: Altern 8@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Penthe "Mod.Penthe"
A promotion mod!
@{b}The Problem@{ub} pays their respects to 'Penthe BBS #1'
150 BPM!!! You'll like this for sure!
Lots of very good drums in here, so no reason why you shouldn't have this!
If you like it hard: Get It!
@ENDNODE

@NODE Talk "Mod.Talk"
A mod about 'The Amazing Way In Wich A Human Communicates.' 
It's very heavy, it's very good and it is composed by @{b}The Problem@{ub}...
Uses samples that were coinsedently sampled during a TV program. It just
happened, and it was responseble for a VERY C00L module indeed!
Uses Breakbeats as well as the normal boom-boom beat.
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Spectacle "Mod.Spectacle" 
Fabulous module...of course!
No Breakbeats in this mod, wich means that you can expect something a little
more to the @{"mellow" LINK Mellow} side of House. The beat seems to be quite popular too.
Just listen, it's high quality all the way, with a little surprise at the
end!
Great!!!
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Enraptor "Mod.Enraptor"
And now for something completely different!
Yes, yes, yes!!! We did it again, another fab mod! With a good drum part,
and with vocals by the (by now) well know @{"WANDA" LINK Wanda}!!!
This was created because of the fact that Wanda was now an official member
of @{b}The Problem@{ub}. The title is randomly picked. Sorry for that!
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Cappella "Mod.U_Got_2_Let_Music"
After a long time, @{b}The Problem@{ub} releases another replication mod!
This time Cappella was the lucky group!!! We used 38(!!!) Samples by 
combining some of them into one sample! The mod was created after one of
the member of @{b}The Problem@{ub} got the single. It seemed impossible to
do, but when it was finnished, it sounded pretty good! 
So....here is:
@{b}
Original Title : U Got 2 Let The Music
Original Artist: Cappella@{ub}
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Twilight "Mod.Twilight-Zone"
Breakbeats are back!
Created to onor the great @{"'TwilightZone BBS'" LINK BBS1}.
As U should know by now, The Twilight Zone is our official support BBS!
It has all our modz. And now we bring U The Twilight Zone Theme!
After 3 modz without, we used breakbeats again, AND HOW! Listen 4 your self
and call: The Twilight Zone! (Mention this guide)
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Doop "Mod.Doop_van_Doop"
Yes, yes, yes!!! Another remake!
@{b}The Problem@{ub} proudly presents: Doop - Doop - Doop
This module was created a long time before the track became popular.
It was rereleased a few months later in a *STUPID* remix.
This mod is the replication of the first release in the Urge 2 Merge Mix!
It is MUCH MUCH MUCH better! Guarranteed!
@{b}
Original Title : Doop
Original Artist: Doop@{ub}
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Wanda2 "Mod.Wanda2"
The longest module @{b}The Problem@{ub} ever made.
There are two completely different parts. Part 1 and....Part 2.
The first one is sort of a ReMix of the original Wanda Module, though the
only thing that is still in tact is the @{"Wanda" LINK Wanda} Voice, from the commercial.
The more expirienced Problem Listener, will even recognize the Piano in
this mix (in the second half of the first part!)

The second is a *@{"MELLOW" LINK Mellow}* part.
This part is also available as a standalone module, called Mellow Infuence!
It's very cool, and super addictive. Once you hear this, you will not want
to stop!

Total playing time (both parts) is 
over 9 minutes (ALL 63 Patterns!), and the time is really worth it!!!
@ENDNODE

@NODE BellsOfNY "Mod.BellsOfNY"
Wow, what a slammer!
It's a replication of the 12" and it's great!!!
The module is about the biggest (in size) of all our mods and there's
a very nice surprice in it... just listen and you'll hear!
This module is aimed at the @{"Mellow" LINK Mellow} fanatics. We replicated the WHOLE track,
wich can't be called short...
@{b}
Original Title : Bells of New York
Original Artist: Slo Moshun@{ub}
@ENDNODE
